131	
132	Altum supports `POST /v1/chat/completions`, `POST /v1/responses`, and
133	`GET /v1/models`. Persistent RLM memory uses `metadata.thread_id`,
134	`X-Altum-Thread`, or the OpenAI `user` field, falling back to `default`.
135	
136	By default, Altum connects to the Railway-hosted Bifrost gateway at
137	`https://bifrost.dio.computer/v1/` and mirrors
138	`https://bifrost.dio.computer/v1/models` from its own `/v1/models` endpoint.
139	Override this with `--base-url` and `--models-url` if you want to point Altum at
140	another OpenAI-compatible provider.
141	
142	### Claude Code Integration
143	
144	```bash
145	claude mcp add altum --transport stdio -- /path/to/target/release/altum serve
146	```
147	
148	## CLI Reference
149	
150	```
151	altum [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>
152	
153	Options:
154	  --model <MODEL>           Root LLM model [default: anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6]
155	  --sub-model <MODEL>       Sub-RLM model [default: anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001]
156	  --base-url <URL>          OpenAI-compatible provider base URL [default: https://bifrost.dio.computer/v1/]
157	  --api-key <KEY>           API key (or set ALTUM_API_KEY env var)
158	  --max-iterations <N>      Max iterations per RLM level [default: 10]
159	  --max-depth <N>           Max recursion depth [default: 2]
160	  --policy-profile <NAME>   Prompt policy profile [default: baseline]
161	  --policy-config <PATH>    Policy config JSON [default: config/prompt_policies.json]
162	  --inject-policy-into-context
163	                            Prepend active policy into runtime context
164	  --depth-enforcement <MODE>
165	                            Depth gate mode: off|soft|strict [default: off]
166	  --require-min-depth <N>   Strict mode: minimum depth reached
167	  --require-min-recursive-calls <N>
168	                            Strict mode: minimum recursive llm_query calls
169	  --data-dir <DIR>          Data directory for context [default: data]
170	  -v, --verbose             Verbose logging to stderr
171	
172	Commands:
173	  query   One-shot query against a context file
174	  chat    Interactive chat with persistent thread context
175	  store   Append text to a thread's context store
176	  serve   Run as an MCP server over stdio or streamable HTTP
177	  serve-openai
178	          Run an OpenAI-compatible HTTP server for agent base_url integrations
179	```
180	
181	`serve` options:
182	
183	```text
184	  --transport <stdio|streamable-http>  MCP transport [default: stdio]
185	  --bind <HOST:PORT>                   Bind address for HTTP transport [default: 127.0.0.1:3000]
186	  --path <PATH>                        Route path for HTTP transport [default: /mcp]
187	```
188	
189	`serve-openai` options:
190	
191	```text
192	  --bind <HOST:PORT>                   Bind address [default: 127.0.0.1:3000]
193	  --models-url <URL>                   Models endpoint to expose from /v1/models
194	```
195	
196	## Multi-Provider Support
197	
198	Altum uses the [genai](https://github.com/jeremychone/rust-genai) crate for LLM access. Providers are auto-detected from model names:
199	
200	| Model prefix | Provider | Env var |
201	|---|---|---|
202	| `gpt-*`, `o1*`, `o3*` | OpenAI | `OPENAI_API_KEY` |
203	| `claude*` | Anthropic | `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` |
204	| `gemini*` | Google | `GEMINI_API_KEY` |
205	| `grok*` | xAI | `XAI_API_KEY` |
206	| Custom/unknown | Ollama (local) | - |
207	
208	The default endpoint is the Railway-hosted Bifrost gateway:
209	
210	```bash
211	export ALTUM_API_KEY=sk-...
212	altum query "hello"
213	```
214	
215	For another OpenAI-compatible provider, use `--base-url` to set the endpoint:
216	
217	```bash
218	export ALTUM_API_KEY=sk-...
219	altum --base-url https://api.synthetic.com/v1 --model minimax query "hello"
220	```

